\n        { \"q\": \"Is SpeechLive suitable for healthcare environments?\", \"a\": \"Yes. SpeechLive stores data on Microsoft Azure with regional options, publishes security and privacy documentation, and is widely used in medical practices for clinical documentation workflows.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Can I use SpeechLive with my existing Philips hardware?\", \"a\": \"Yes. SpeechLive is compatible with the Philips SpeechMike range, SpeechOne wireless microphone, and the DataVoice smartphone app. Existing Philips hardware users can migrate to the cloud workflow without replacing equipment.\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"dragon-professional-anywhere\",\n      \"heroImageKey\": \"dpa-hero\",\n      \"featureImageKey\": \"dpa-feature\",\n      \"badge\": \"Cloud Speech Recognition\",\n      \"navLabel\": \"Dragon Professional Anywhere\",\n      \"title\": \"Dragon Professional Anywhere\",\n      \"metaTitle\": \"Dragon Professional Anywhere Australia | Cloud Speech Recognition | VRA\",\n      \"metaDesc\": \"Dragon Professional Anywhere - cloud-based speech recognition for Windows and Mac. Dictate from any device. No local installation. Subscription licensing. Authorised Australian reseller.\",\n      \"headline\": \"Dragon Professional Anywhere - Speech Recognition in the Cloud\",\n      \"subheadline\": \"The full power of Dragon Professional available in the cloud. Dictate from any Windows or Mac device without installing local software. Cloud-based subscription model.\",\n      \"price\": \"Enquire\",\n      \"priceNote\": \"Annual subscription - volume pricing available\",\n      \"licenceNote\": \"Cloud-based subscription. Unlimited device access. Managed via web account.\",\n      \"installLimit\": \"Unlimited devices\",\n      \"bestFor\": \"Enterprises and multi-device users\",\n      \"vraUrl\": \"https://www.voicerecognition.com.au/collections/dragon-professional\",\n      \"ctaText\": \"Enquire About Cloud Pricing\",\n      \"features\": [\n        \"Full Dragon Professional 16 features in the cloud\",\n        \"Works on Windows and Mac - no platform limitations\",\n        \"Install on unlimited devices under subscription\",\n        \"Requires internet connection for use\",\n        \"Custom vocabulary and user profiles in the cloud\",\n        \"Deep integration with Microsoft 365, Google Docs, and web applications\",\n        \"Enterprise deployment options available\",\n        \"Annual subscription with flexible renewal options\",\n        \"Centralised user management for team deployments\"\n      ],\n      \"faqs\": [\n        { \"q\": \"Do I need internet to use Dragon Professional Anywhere?\", \"a\": \"Yes. Dragon Professional Anywhere is cloud-based and requires an active internet connection to use.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Can I use it on Mac and Windows?\", \"a\": \"Yes. Dragon Professional Anywhere works on both Windows and Mac computers.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"How many devices can I install on?\", \"a\": \"With the subscription, you can install on unlimited devices under your account. However, only one concurrent session is typically allowed - check your licence terms.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"What's the difference between Dragon Professional 16 and Dragon Professional Anywhere?\", \"a\": \"Dragon Professional 16 is locally installed for Windows only and works offline. Dragon Professional Anywhere is cloud-based, works on Windows and Mac, requires internet, and is subscription-based.\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"dictation-hardware\",\n      \"heroImageKey\": \"hw-hero\",\n      \"featureImageKey\": \"feature-hardware\",\n      \"badge\": \"Recorders & Microphones\",\n      \"navLabel\": \"Dictation Hardware\",\n      \"title\": \"Dictation Hardware & Equipment\",\n      \"metaTitle\": \"Dictation Recorders & Microphones | Philips Olympus | VRA Australia\",\n      \"metaDesc\": \"Professional dictation hardware - Philips and Olympus digital voice recorders, USB microphones, foot pedals, headsets. Healthcare and legal-grade equipment. Australian stock and support.\",\n      \"headline\": \"Professional Dictation Hardware\",\n      \"subheadline\": \"Complete dictation equipment - digital voice recorders, professional microphones, foot pedals, and headsets from Philips and Olympus. Healthcare and legal-grade security features.\",\n      \"price\": \"From $50\",\n      \"priceNote\": \"Foot pedals - Recorders and mics priced individually\",\n      \"licenceNote\": \"One-off hardware purchase. Local Australian stock and support available.\",\n      \"installLimit\": \"Recorders, pedals, headsets\",\n      \"bestFor\": \"Medical and legal\",\n      \"vraUrl\": \"https://www.voicerecognition.com.au/collections/voice-recorder\",\n      \"ctaText\": \"Browse Dictation Equipment\",\n      \"features\": [\n        \"Philips digital voice recorders - DS series with encryption and cloud sync\",\n        \"Olympus dictation recorders - professional models with premium audio quality\",\n        \"Professional USB and wireless microphones for desktop dictation\",\n        \"SpeechMike microphones - optimised for Dragon Professional use\",\n        \"Foot pedals for hands-free transcription workflow control (play, pause, rewind)\",\n        \"Professional headsets and noise-cancelling microphones\",\n        \"256-bit AES encryption on selected professional models\",\n        \"Cloud connectivity options for modern hybrid workflows\",\n        \"Local Australian stock and technical support\"\n      ],\n      \"faqs\": [\n        { \"q\": \"What dictation recorder should I use for healthcare?\", \"a\": \"Philips SpeechMike or SpeechOne devices are widely used with Dragon Medical One. Olympus DS series recorders are popular for clinicians who prefer remote dictation. The choice depends on your EMR integration and workflow.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Can I use a regular microphone with Dragon Professional?\", \"a\": \"Yes, most USB microphones work with Dragon Professional. However, dedicated dictation microphones like SpeechMike are optimised for speech recognition and typically offer better accuracy.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"What is a foot pedal used for?\", \"a\": \"A foot pedal provides hands-free control of audio playback during transcription - play, pause, rewind, and fast-forward. This allows typists and transcriptionists to keep both hands on the keyboard.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Do you have professional recorders with encryption?\", \"a\": \"Yes. Philips DS series and Olympus professional models include 256-bit AES encryption for healthcare and legal environments requiring data security.\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"transcription-services\",\n      \"heroImageKey\": \"ts-hero\",\n      \"featureImageKey\": \"ts-feature\",\n      \"badge\": \"Professional Services\",\n      \"navLabel\": \"Transcription Services\",\n      \"title\": \"Transcription Services\",\n      \"metaTitle\": \"Professional Transcription Services Australia | Medical, Legal | VRA\",\n      \"metaDesc\": \"Professional transcription services - medical, legal, and general business transcription by experienced Australian transcriptionists. Secure, confidential, quick turnaround.\",\n      \"headline\": \"Professional Transcription Services\",\n      \"subheadline\": \"Experienced Australian transcriptionists providing secure, accurate transcription of medical consultations, legal proceedings, business meetings, and general audio content.\",\n      \"price\": \"Enquire\",\n      \"priceNote\": \"Per-minute or per-project pricing - volume discounts available\",\n      \"licenceNote\": \"One-off or ongoing transcription services. Confidentiality agreements included.\",\n      \"installLimit\": \"Service-based\",\n      \"bestFor\": \"Organisations requiring human-quality professional transcription\",\n      \"vraUrl\": \"https://www.voicerecognition.com.au/pages/transcription-services\",\n      \"ctaText\": \"Request Transcription Quote\",\n      \"features\": [\n        \"Medical transcription - clinical notes, consultation recordings, medical reports\",\n        \"Legal transcription - interview transcripts, court proceedings, legal correspondence\",\n        \"Business transcription - meeting minutes, conference recordings, presentations\",\n        \"General transcription - podcasts, interviews, focus groups\",\n        \"Experienced Australian transcriptionists with industry expertise\",\n        \"Confidentiality agreements and secure data handling\",\n        \"Quick turnaround times - same-day to next-day for rush requests\",\n        \"Quality assurance - review and verification of all transcripts\",\n        \"Flexible pricing - per-minute, per-project, or volume-based\"\n      ],\n      \"faqs\": [\n        { \"q\": \"How long does transcription take?\", \"a\": \"Standard turnaround is 2-3 business days. Rush transcription is available for same-day or next-day delivery at premium rates.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Are transcripts confidential?\", \"a\": \"Yes. All transcription work is covered by confidentiality agreements. We handle healthcare, legal, and business-sensitive content securely.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"What file formats do you accept?\", \"a\": \"We accept MP3, WAV, WMA, M4A, and most common audio formats. Video files can also be processed. Contact us with your specific format.\" },\n        { \"q\": \"Do you provide specialist medical or legal transcription?\", \"a\": \"Yes. We employ transcriptionists with medical and legal industry experience. Healthcare and legal terminology is standard for our specialists.\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"benefits\": [\n    { \"title\": \"Hardware and software expertise\", \"body\": \"We cover the full dictation workflow - from Philips and Olympus voice recorders through to Dragon speech recognition software and cloud AI transcription. One contact, complete solution.\" },\n    { \"title\": \"Healthcare and legal focus\", \"body\": \"Most of our clients work in healthcare, legal or government. Our team understands medical documentation requirements, legal confidentiality, and secure enterprise dictation environments.\" },\n    { \"title\": \"Modern and traditional workflows\", \"body\": \"Not everyone is ready to move to cloud AI. We support traditional dictation recorder workflows alongside modern Dragon and cloud speech solutions - whichever works for your team.\" },\n    { \"title\": \"Australian support\", \"body\": \"Local deployment support from Voice Recognition Australia. Real people who understand your workflow, not a support ticket queue in another timezone.\" }\n  ],\n  \"proofPoints\": [\n    \"25 years of Australian dictation and speech recognition expertise\",\n    \"Dragon authorised reseller since product launch in Australia\",\n    \"Philips and Olympus hardware specialists\",\n    \"Healthcare, legal and government deployment experience\"\n  ],\n  \"faqs\": [\n    { \"q\": \"What is the difference between Dragon and a dictation recorder?\", \"a\": \"Dragon software converts your speech to text in real time as you dictate into a computer or microphone. A digital dictation recorder captures your voice as an audio file, which is then transcribed later - either manually by a typist or via software. Many professionals use both: a recorder in the field, Dragon at the desk.\" },\n    { \"q\": \"Do I need Dragon software or is cloud speech recognition enough?\", \"a\": \"It depends on your workflow. Dragon Professional works offline, has deep Windows application integration, and can automate complex tasks by voice. <a href=\\\"https://www.speechrecognition.cloud\\\" style=\\\"color:#16a34a;font-weight:600\\\">speech to text software</a> from SpeechRecognition.cloud is a lightweight installed Windows app that works in any application - the base package is free and it is a cost-effective way to get started. We can help you work out which approach suits your situation.\" },\n    { \"q\": \"What dictation hardware do you recommend for healthcare?\", \"a\": \"For healthcare workflows, Philips SpeechMike and SpeechOne devices are widely used with Dragon Medical One. Olympus digital recorders work well for clinicians who prefer to dictate remotely and have audio transcribed. The right choice depends on whether you are dictating directly into an EMR or using a separate transcription workflow.\" },\n    { \"q\": \"Is Dragon Medical One available in Australia?\", \"a\": \"Yes. Dragon Medical One is available through Voice Recognition Australia, an authorised Nuance/Microsoft reseller. It is a cloud-based subscription product designed specifically for healthcare documentation. Pricing is per user per year - contact Voice Recognition Australia for current Australian pricing.\" },\n    { \"q\": \"What is a foot pedal used for in dictation?\", \"a\": \"A foot pedal lets a typist or transcriptionist control audio playback hands-free during transcription - play, pause, rewind and fast-forward using their feet while their hands remain on the keyboard. Philips and Olympus both make foot pedals designed for their respective dictation workflows.\" },\n    { \"q\": \"What is Philips SpeechLive and who is it for?\", \"a\": \"Philips SpeechLive is a cloud-based dictation workflow platform. You dictate on any device - phone, SpeechMike, or web browser - and recordings are securely routed to a transcriptionist or to Dragon speech recognition for automated conversion. It is widely used in healthcare, legal, and professional services environments that need a managed, auditable dictation workflow.\" }\n  ],\n  \"footerLinks\": [\n    { \"label\": \"About\", \"url\": \"/about\" },\n    { \"label\": \"Privacy Policy\", \"url\": \"/privacy\" },\n    { \"label\": \"Terms\", \"url\": \"/terms\" },\n    { \"label\": \"Contact\", \"url\": \"#final-cta\" }\n  ]\n}\n